1
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:18,000
THE WARRIOR'S WAY (2010)

2
00:00:18,529 --> 00:00:20,920
(male narrator) Okay.
Settle down.

3
00:00:21,003 --> 00:00:22,733
Got your ears open?

4
00:00:24,342 --> 00:00:26,321
(clears throat)

5
00:00:26,404 --> 00:00:29,494
This is the story of a sad flute

6
00:00:29,578 --> 00:00:32,423
a laughin' baby
and a weepin' sword.

7
00:00:40,010 --> 00:00:45,822
A long, long time ago
in a land far, far away,

8
00:00:45,905 --> 00:00:48,502
there lived a warrior...

9
00:00:48,585 --> 00:00:51,182
warrior with empty eyes.

10
00:02:26,257 --> 00:02:29,555
He'd trained his entire life
for one purpose.

11
00:02:32,113 --> 00:02:35,947
To be the greatest swordsman
in the history of mankind.

12
00:03:20,598 --> 00:03:23,483
He'd just achieved
his life's ambition,

13
00:03:23,567 --> 00:03:26,245
but his heart felt emptier
than ever.

14
00:03:29,504 --> 00:03:33,338
These two clans had been warrin'
for 500 years.

15
00:03:33,421 --> 00:03:36,347
And they vowed to keep on warrin'
until one of them

16
00:03:36,431 --> 00:03:38,822
didn't have a single man
left above Styx.

17
00:03:51,645 --> 00:03:53,293
(giggles)

18
00:03:59,683 --> 00:04:01,950
(coos, cries)

19
00:04:07,106 --> 00:04:09,372
(coos, giggles)

20
00:04:09,455 --> 00:04:11,228
And so now, here he was,

21
00:04:11,311 --> 00:04:14,236
peerin' down
at this very last of his enemy.

22
00:04:14,320 --> 00:04:16,051
(baby coos, laughs)

23
00:04:24,505 --> 00:04:27,637
When that
little warrior princess giggled,

24
00:04:27,720 --> 00:04:29,780
it did somethin' to him inside.

25
00:04:32,213 --> 00:04:33,945
But this was no time for feelin'.

26
00:05:03,467 --> 00:05:05,732
For when spared that baby's life,

27
00:05:05,815 --> 00:05:09,732
he put his name at the top
of his own clan's death list.

28
00:06:09,515 --> 00:06:13,720
With nothin' but the clothes on his back
and the baby in his arms,

29
00:06:13,804 --> 00:06:19,080
he decided to pay a visit to an old
warrior friend in a faraway land.

30
00:07:51,393 --> 00:07:52,794
Hey, Johnny.

31
00:07:54,404 --> 00:07:57,082
I don't like your stinkin' face.

32
00:07:57,165 --> 00:07:59,144
Easy, Ronald.

33
00:07:59,228 --> 00:08:02,772
The name's Eight-Ball.
Like in the game.

34
00:08:02,854 --> 00:08:05,080
Good luck for some,
bad luck for others.

35
00:08:05,164 --> 00:08:08,750
How can I assist you,
my friend from the mystical East?

36
00:08:12,338 --> 00:08:13,987
Uh-oh.

37
00:08:18,482 --> 00:08:20,666
Haven't been here
since Smiley kicked the bucket.

38
00:08:22,274 --> 00:08:25,036
Was a 3-day wait
just to get your shirts pressed.

39
00:08:30,025 --> 00:08:31,385
(laughs)

40
00:08:31,469 --> 00:08:34,685
For a guy who cleaned sheets all day,
he sure liked to make a mess

41
00:08:34,768 --> 00:08:37,240
in the after-hours,
if you know what I mean.

42
00:08:39,137 --> 00:08:40,209
See you in the morning.

43
00:08:59,464 --> 00:09:01,978
(man) You came to me
to be strong.

44
00:09:05,360 --> 00:09:08,285
I have made you the strongest.

45
00:09:12,244 --> 00:09:15,830
She will always be the enemy.

46
00:09:27,787 --> 00:09:29,849
(baby crying in distance)

47
00:09:56,444 --> 00:09:58,957
(bellows)

48
00:10:06,874 --> 00:10:08,440
Here it is.

49
00:10:08,523 --> 00:10:10,543
Just rub some on your shoulder.

50
00:10:11,449 --> 00:10:14,418
Smiley's Oriental cure-all.
Works like a charm.

51
00:10:14,502 --> 00:10:15,530
(crying)

52
00:10:15,614 --> 00:10:17,345
Now, honey,
I didn't forget about you.

53
00:10:18,913 --> 00:10:22,582
It's alright there. It's okay.
Ssh, ssh, ssh.

54
00:10:22,665 --> 00:10:26,911
Sorry about the tap I gave ya.
I thought you knew the sword.

55
00:10:26,994 --> 00:10:31,939
Smiley was always yabberin' on about
a guy who was gonna roll into town.

56
00:10:32,023 --> 00:10:36,557
But I shoulda figgered.
What do you call her?

57
00:10:36,641 --> 00:10:38,248
I do not know.

58
00:10:38,331 --> 00:10:40,640
Oh. She's not yours?

59
00:10:40,723 --> 00:10:42,785
Where's her folks?

60
00:10:42,867 --> 00:10:44,844
Dead.

61
00:10:54,906 --> 00:10:58,162
Oo-ee, best we find you
another diaper.

62
00:10:58,244 --> 00:10:59,481
Alright.

63
00:11:01,752 --> 00:11:04,057
Smiley like
your uncle or something?

64
00:11:04,141 --> 00:11:05,871
Friend.

65
00:11:05,955 --> 00:11:09,211
Well, if you were his friend,
maybe he would like for you

66
00:11:09,337 --> 00:11:10,573
to take over his laundry.

67
00:11:10,657 --> 00:11:14,365
- Do not know how.
- So I'll teach ya.

68
00:11:14,449 --> 00:11:16,386
I always done the laundry
around here.

69
00:11:16,469 --> 00:11:18,900
That's how I repaid Smiley
for teaching me the sword.

70
00:11:18,984 --> 00:11:21,663
Tell you what I'm gonna do.

71
00:11:21,746 --> 00:11:24,921
You stay here, I'll teach you how
to tie a diaper properly.

72
00:11:25,004 --> 00:11:28,218
We'll be partners, 60:40.
You are the 40.

73
00:11:29,580 --> 00:11:31,476
Alright now,
time to get to work.

74
00:11:34,733 --> 00:11:38,073
Dang, you're slower
than molasses in January.

75
00:11:43,392 --> 00:11:45,453
(fly buzzing)

76
00:12:04,625 --> 00:12:06,809
You clean that real good,
yellow boy.

77
00:12:06,893 --> 00:12:09,035
As clean
as Snow White's panties...

78
00:12:09,118 --> 00:12:14,066
If I find the smallest bit
of condor crap on my fancy duds...

79
00:12:14,149 --> 00:12:18,643
- Well, we gonna have us...
- (crunch)

80
00:12:18,726 --> 00:12:21,734
Didn't I tell you I'd rip 'em off
if you don't watch yourself?

81
00:12:21,817 --> 00:12:22,847
Let go, evil midget!

82
00:12:22,930 --> 00:12:25,239
Come on, Eight-Ball,
we were just havin' us some fun.

83
00:12:25,322 --> 00:12:27,548
- Really?
- Ah! (grunts)

84
00:12:27,631 --> 00:12:31,094
Okay... okay...
Let go.

85
00:12:31,178 --> 00:12:33,691
- (laughs)
- Get outta here!

86
00:12:38,308 --> 00:12:40,741
How 'bout a home-cooked meal
for you and your little 'un?

87
00:12:44,946 --> 00:12:49,235
Once that Ferris wheel is finished,
it's gonna bring everybody rushin' back,

88
00:12:49,319 --> 00:12:52,822
And then we can take the word
"travelling" out of "travelling circus."

89
00:12:52,905 --> 00:12:54,512
Hey, Ron.

90
00:12:54,595 --> 00:12:58,305
(slurring) Welcome to the
Eighth Wonder ofthe World!

91
00:12:58,388 --> 00:13:00,655
Get down here!
The chow bell ringin'!

92
00:13:07,130 --> 00:13:08,366
Ha!

93
00:13:48,812 --> 00:13:50,626
(light applause)

94
00:13:50,709 --> 00:13:53,223
(woman) Bravo, bravo.

95
00:13:58,831 --> 00:14:00,726
(laughs, applause)

96
00:14:04,438 --> 00:14:06,499
Gonna grab some vittles with us?

97
00:14:06,582 --> 00:14:08,806
No thanks.
Not hungry.

98
00:14:08,890 --> 00:14:12,560
I-I-I b-baked a cake.

99
00:14:15,528 --> 00:14:17,920
Come on, Ron!

100
00:14:18,003 --> 00:14:20,804
What the hell's up with her?

101
00:14:27,733 --> 00:14:31,607
You, I knew you was trouble the moment
you walked into this...

102
00:14:31,690 --> 00:14:33,668
(gurgles)

103
00:14:37,463 --> 00:14:40,059
(snores, laughter)

104
00:14:45,915 --> 00:14:48,841
(woman singing operatically)

105
00:15:14,693 --> 00:15:16,755
(squeals)

106
00:15:33,493 --> 00:15:35,678
Sounds even better from inside.

107
00:15:37,905 --> 00:15:40,955
(singing continues)

108
00:15:44,419 --> 00:15:47,099
You ever seen
one ofthese before?

109
00:15:49,078 --> 00:15:53,200
The sound it's makin'?
It's called "opera."

110
00:15:53,283 --> 00:15:56,828
Day my poppa found his first chunk
of gold,

111
00:15:56,953 --> 00:15:59,262
he went out and bought this thing.

112
00:16:04,787 --> 00:16:07,178
Listen.
Here's my favorite part.

113
00:16:42,305 --> 00:16:46,675
(narrator) So at the edge of the desert,
in a busted town full of broken people,

114
00:16:46,759 --> 00:16:52,572
the warrior began to learn stuff
he shoulda learned a long time ago.

115
00:16:52,655 --> 00:16:54,549
(squishing)

116
00:17:04,858 --> 00:17:06,341
No, no! Rough!

117
00:17:08,982 --> 00:17:11,577
Like the joy
of gettin' dirty things clean.

118
00:17:17,558 --> 00:17:19,701
(laughs)

119
00:17:24,319 --> 00:17:25,802
Yes!

120
00:17:29,844 --> 00:17:32,480
Woo hoo! That's me!
(laughs) Thank you!

121
00:17:32,564 --> 00:17:35,202
I told you to aim at the line,
not at the coin!

122
00:17:35,286 --> 00:17:36,357
All right! (laughs)

123
00:17:36,440 --> 00:17:39,448
He also learned the joy of losing.

124
00:17:39,532 --> 00:17:42,830
You're gonna need blood and bone of
about 100 dead buffaloes as fertilizer.

125
00:17:42,914 --> 00:17:45,181
Smiley always tried
to get something to grow.

126
00:17:45,264 --> 00:17:46,911
Never, ever lasted too long.

127
00:17:52,148 --> 00:17:54,992
He learned you could be happy
workin' with folks.

128
00:17:57,632 --> 00:18:00,558
And findin' the simple peace
in some private time

129
00:18:00,641 --> 00:18:03,031
after a hard day's work.

130
00:18:03,115 --> 00:18:04,764
(door bell chimes)

131
00:18:04,847 --> 00:18:06,289
What's takin' you so long?

132
00:18:20,308 --> 00:18:23,152
Come on, Skinny!
You gonna miss it. Come on.

133
00:18:24,966 --> 00:18:27,028
(door bell chimes, door closes)

134
00:18:33,460 --> 00:18:35,274
(train whistle blows)

135
00:18:35,358 --> 00:18:38,819
And he found that it's nice
to have a few friends around

136
00:18:38,903 --> 00:18:40,798
when the sun goes down.

137
00:18:48,304 --> 00:18:52,219
But most of all, the warrior learned
there's a heck of a lot more pleasure

138
00:18:52,303 --> 00:18:56,341
makin' things grow
than there is in cuttin' 'em down.

139
00:19:04,052 --> 00:19:06,444
(laughter)

140
00:19:06,527 --> 00:19:08,752
You bunch of pups!
Gimme back that goddamn bottle!

141
00:19:19,679 --> 00:19:21,368
You win.
Show me what you got.

142
00:19:24,708 --> 00:19:27,512
God damn!
I shoulda never taught you this game!

143
00:19:27,595 --> 00:19:29,573
You a shark with a poker face.

144
00:19:52,292 --> 00:19:53,651
What happened to her?

145
00:20:18,431 --> 00:20:22,263
(woman whimpers) Please!
Help me!

146
00:20:22,347 --> 00:20:24,202
- Help me!
- Lynne!

147
00:20:24,285 --> 00:20:27,500
- Please! Let her go!
- Someone, help me!

148
00:20:27,584 --> 00:20:30,387
- Eight-Ball!
- Lynne!!

149
00:20:41,684 --> 00:20:42,796
(man) Hungry?

150
00:20:45,146 --> 00:20:46,341
No?

151
00:21:14,420 --> 00:21:16,028
Pretty thing.

152
00:21:42,868 --> 00:21:44,723
Aagh!

153
00:21:44,806 --> 00:21:46,867
Agh! Aah!

154
00:21:52,475 --> 00:21:54,288
Damn you!

155
00:22:15,109 --> 00:22:16,428
(pistol cocks)

156
00:22:22,036 --> 00:22:25,128
Noooo!

157
00:22:25,212 --> 00:22:28,219
(grunting, crowd murmuring)

158
00:22:30,900 --> 00:22:33,704
No! Lynne! Lynne!

159
00:22:39,559 --> 00:22:40,836
Agh!

160
00:22:47,682 --> 00:22:49,742
No!!

161
00:22:54,402 --> 00:22:56,009
(woman sobs, gunshots)

162
00:22:56,092 --> 00:22:57,493
No!!

163
00:23:17,285 --> 00:23:19,962
Only thing was,
when we went to bury her,

164
00:23:20,046 --> 00:23:21,448
she was still breathing.

165
00:23:22,686 --> 00:23:25,074
Never known nobody
that close to kickin' it.

166
00:23:26,808 --> 00:23:32,042
We didn't know what to do wit' her,
if'n she was gonna live or die.

167
00:23:32,125 --> 00:23:35,590
So we just put her in bed
and waited.

168
00:23:35,673 --> 00:23:38,475
Two days,
and she was eating soup.

169
00:23:38,559 --> 00:23:41,608
By the day three, she was already
sitting up somehow

170
00:23:41,692 --> 00:23:43,712
and slinging daggers
at the wall.

171
00:23:45,691 --> 00:23:46,844
But God ain't fair.

172
00:23:46,927 --> 00:23:50,226
And some people
just ain't cut out for the knife.

173
00:24:09,893 --> 00:24:13,809
Dang it.
My arm ain't worth a damn.

174
00:24:15,996 --> 00:24:17,519
It is not your arm.

175
00:24:24,447 --> 00:24:26,548
What'd you say?

176
00:24:26,633 --> 00:24:28,280
Ouch!

177
00:24:31,250 --> 00:24:32,527
Now you sure about this?

178
00:24:32,610 --> 00:24:35,288
'Cause I'm not so good
with my eyes open.

179
00:24:35,373 --> 00:24:37,267
Throw.

180
00:24:44,237 --> 00:24:45,721
I can't do it.

181
00:24:45,804 --> 00:24:48,607
Do not talk. Focus.

182
00:24:48,691 --> 00:24:50,874
It is your heart that shakes.

183
00:25:04,562 --> 00:25:05,882
You dead?

184
00:25:05,965 --> 00:25:07,161
Not yet.

185
00:25:28,146 --> 00:25:30,743
Sure you're not fountainin' blood
or anything, are ya?

186
00:25:33,877 --> 00:25:35,154
Oh, shit!

187
00:25:46,946 --> 00:25:49,791
(laughs) Ha!

188
00:25:49,875 --> 00:25:51,152
I did it!

189
00:25:53,956 --> 00:25:55,935
Thank you,
Mr. Sad Flute.

190
00:25:58,616 --> 00:26:00,551
Smiley told me everything.

191
00:26:00,635 --> 00:26:02,655
I just taught you to focus.

192
00:26:15,230 --> 00:26:17,168
Why you do that?

193
00:26:59,923 --> 00:27:03,138
Okay.
I've always been dyin' to know.

194
00:27:03,222 --> 00:27:05,158
Why are y'all called
The Sad Flutes?

195
00:27:10,066 --> 00:27:13,157
So you got lady Sad Flutes,
too?

196
00:27:13,241 --> 00:27:15,508
Sad Flutinas or somethin'?

197
00:27:17,693 --> 00:27:19,341
Yes.

198
00:27:19,424 --> 00:27:22,516
Wow! That's nice.

199
00:27:22,600 --> 00:27:25,979
Jumpin' in the moonlight and kissin'

200
00:27:26,062 --> 00:27:30,103
as you both fly under the stars
to the tunes of The Sad Flutes...

201
00:27:30,186 --> 00:27:35,709
We are called Sad Flutes
because when you cut the throat,

202
00:27:35,792 --> 00:27:39,131
the last sound is like a sad flute.

203
00:27:41,194 --> 00:27:42,347
Dang!

204
00:27:42,430 --> 00:27:46,552
Skinny, sure know how to throw
a dead cat into a party room, don't ya?

205
00:27:52,285 --> 00:27:54,179
Why'd you become a Sad Flute?

206
00:27:57,893 --> 00:27:59,747
To be strong.

207
00:27:59,829 --> 00:28:01,023
That it?

208
00:28:07,332 --> 00:28:10,796
My father was working in the field.

209
00:28:10,879 --> 00:28:12,364
I was helping him.

210
00:28:14,424 --> 00:28:17,269
A swordsman came.

211
00:28:17,352 --> 00:28:18,919
Killed my father.

212
00:28:19,002 --> 00:28:22,216
Just to test his sword.

213
00:28:24,115 --> 00:28:26,340
That musta hurt you
somethin' bad.

214
00:28:26,423 --> 00:28:30,421
Not hurt. Angry.

215
00:28:30,504 --> 00:28:32,606
Course.

216
00:28:32,689 --> 00:28:34,586
No.

217
00:28:34,669 --> 00:28:38,585
I was angry at my father.

218
00:28:55,037 --> 00:28:58,704
Here. Take it.

219
00:28:58,787 --> 00:29:02,745
It's a present.
My momma gave it to me.

220
00:29:02,829 --> 00:29:07,568
She said, "If you hold it
over your heart when you're sad,

221
00:29:07,653 --> 00:29:09,879
it takes away all your sadness."

222
00:29:11,321 --> 00:29:14,124
It works.

223
00:29:14,208 --> 00:29:15,650
Kinda.

224
00:29:18,330 --> 00:29:19,608
Present?

225
00:29:19,691 --> 00:29:21,422
Yeah.

226
00:29:26,165 --> 00:29:28,225
(footsteps approaching)

227
00:29:33,792 --> 00:29:36,265
(whimpers)

228
00:29:36,349 --> 00:29:38,903
(dog yips)

229
00:29:43,976 --> 00:29:46,531
That is your only friend here.

230
00:29:46,614 --> 00:29:48,592
Take good care of it.

231
00:29:48,675 --> 00:29:50,201
Yes, master.

232
00:29:58,158 --> 00:29:59,642
Oh, tarnations.

233
00:29:59,724 --> 00:30:02,198
Only to protect,
not kill.

234
00:30:02,281 --> 00:30:04,425
What am I gonna kill in this town,
an armadillo?

235
00:30:06,363 --> 00:30:08,012
Is that what I think it is?

236
00:30:24,751 --> 00:30:27,018
You've sealed it.

237
00:30:27,102 --> 00:30:29,327
So they cannot hear.

238
00:30:29,410 --> 00:30:31,595
Hear what?

239
00:30:31,678 --> 00:30:33,039
The weeping.

240
00:30:35,099 --> 00:30:38,851
Of all the souls I have taken.

241
00:30:42,357 --> 00:30:43,469
Who's listenin'?

242
00:30:43,552 --> 00:30:47,015
My past.

243
00:30:47,098 --> 00:30:48,622
And if it hears?

244
00:30:51,014 --> 00:30:52,664
No more music.

245
00:31:03,425 --> 00:31:05,898
This is a big country.
Where do we look?

246
00:31:08,867 --> 00:31:10,845
Do not look.

247
00:31:10,929 --> 00:31:13,648
We listen.

248
00:31:13,732 --> 00:31:15,299
He will show.

249
00:31:52,858 --> 00:31:55,580
Think ofthe sword
as part of the body.

250
00:31:56,405 --> 00:31:59,001
Like a finger.
Like a tooth.

251
00:31:59,085 --> 00:32:03,331
Rather think of it like metal
slicin' through a herd of buffalo!

252
00:32:10,052 --> 00:32:12,030
Show me what Smiley taught you.

253
00:32:23,203 --> 00:32:25,429
You do not have the power.

254
00:32:25,513 --> 00:32:28,645
Well, thank you very much.
I did not know that.

255
00:32:28,728 --> 00:32:30,212
But you are fast.

256
00:32:30,295 --> 00:32:32,809
Just have to be faster.

257
00:32:34,832 --> 00:32:36,148
Ouch!

258
00:32:37,221 --> 00:32:41,468
Ouch! Is this 'cause of yesterday?
'Cause I said I was sorry!

259
00:32:41,551 --> 00:32:43,817
